<?xml version="1.0"?>
<Container version="2">
  <Name>Arrgo</Name>
  <Repository>justbri/arrgo_oss:latest</Repository>
  <Registry>https://hub.docker.com/r/justbri/arrgo_oss</Registry>
  <Network>bridge</Network>
  <MyIP/>
  <Shell>sh</Shell>
  <Privileged>false</Privileged>
  <Support>https://github.com/justbri/Arrgo_OSS/issues</Support>
  <Project>https://github.com/justbri/Arrgo_OSS</Project>
  <Overview>
    Arrgo is a lightweight, high-performance media management tool designed to provide a modern, consolidated alternative to the existing *arr stack. It is specifically optimized for home server environments like Unraid.&#xD;
    &#xD;
    [b]Key Features:[/b]&#xD;
    - [b]Consolidated Management:[/b] Handle both movies and TV shows in one unified interface.&#xD;
    - [b]Automated Workflows:[/b] Automated downloads via qBittorrent, intelligent seeding cleanup, and integrated subtitle fetching.&#xD;
    - [b]Media Server Compatibility:[/b] Automatically organizes and renames files to follow Plex and Jellyfin conventions.&#xD;
    - [b]Lightweight &amp; Fast:[/b] Built with Go and HTMX for minimal resource usage.&#xD;
    &#xD;
    [b]Requirements:[/b]&#xD;
    - A PostgreSQL 16 database.&#xD;
    - qBittorrent for downloads.&#xD;
    - API keys for TMDB and TVDB.&#xD;
  </Overview>
  <Category>MediaApp:Video MediaApp:Management Downloaders:</Category>
  <Changes>
### 2026-02-08
- Initial Unraid CA Template release.
- Added support for PUID/PGID.
- Configured persistent paths for posters and media.
  </Changes>
